        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 27 at 1:57PM EDT by NWS Gray ME</headline>
        <description>At 157 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Goffstown, or 8 miles west of Manchester, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Manchester, Bedford, Goffstown, New Boston, Hooksett, Londonderry,
and Amherst.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 293 between mile markers 2 and 11.
Interstate 93 between mile markers 24 and 27.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
